## 절대 금지 (Prohibitions)
| 금지 | 이유 (ADR/PR/incident) |
|------|------------------------|
| `git commit --no-verify` | bypasses pre-commit linter |
| `--dangerously-skip-permissions` | disables safety hooks |
| `git add -A` / `git add .` | risk committing secrets — explicit filenames only |
| Edit `.env` / SSH keys / `*.pem` | secret exposure |
| Edit linter/type config to silence error | fix the code, not the rule |
| Source files > 300 lines | SRP violation — split |

## Codex-specific notes
- Hooks: `.codex/hooks.json` (covers SessionStart, PreToolUse, PostToolUse, UserPromptSubmit, Stop — Bash-only)
- Sandbox: each task runs in an isolated cloud container; `enableAllProjectMcpServers: false` not applicable (Codex is closed-room by design)
- Async parallel: use `codex cloud exec` for multi-task throughput

## Sync rules

`CLAUDE.md` (Claude Code) and `AGENTS.md` (everyone else) MUST agree on:
- Commands (build/test/lint)
- Prohibitions table (left column)
- ADR location
- Project description

They MAY differ on:
- Tool-specific hook config (Claude Code: `.claude/settings.local.json`; Codex: `.codex/hooks.json`)
- Plan Mode references (Claude Code only)
- MCP server lists (each tool has its own format)

When updating one, update the other. Run `.claude/scripts/drift-scan.sh` to catch divergence.

> Target: ≤50 lines each. If you can derive it from `package.json` / `pyproject.toml` / git log, delete the line.
